Comment (src/composables/useControlOptions/index.ts:22):
**Low — unguarded request race on rapid catalog switches.** `abortPrevious: false` plus no per-request token in `load()` means two loads can be in flight when the source/target catalog is switched quickly. `load()` sets `options.value = []` then `await execute(...)`; if the earlier catalog's response resolves last, its controls overwrite the newer selection — so the Select can show controls that don't belong to `catalogId`.

Same race class the drawer already guards with a monotonic token (`evidenceRequestKey`/`sspRequestKey` in LineageNodeDrawer). Suggest the same here: capture `id` at call time and bail if `toValue(catalogId) !== id` before assigning `options.value`. Low for a PoC / single select, but noting it for consistency.
Replies:
**lisa implementation guidance:** Fix in src/composables/useControlOptions/index.ts load(). Add a module- or closure-scoped monotonic token: `let requestToken = 0;`. In load(): `const token = ++requestToken;` right after capturing `id`. After `await execute(...)` resolves, before assigning options.value, bail if superseded: `if (token !== requestToken) return;` — guard both the success assignment and the finally's `loading.value = false` so a stale load doesn't clear the loading flag of a newer one (only reset loading when `token === requestToken`). Mirror LineageNodeDrawer's evidenceRequestKey pattern. Keep options.value = [] reset at the top (that's the in-flight-newer path).

